			<h3> Applying Tips</h3>
			
			<hr>
			<br><br>
				<h3 style="font-size:18px;text-align:left;color:black">Create a complete and up-to-date profile :</h3>
				<p style="font-size:16px;color:black">Make sure that your profile on the job portal is complete and up-to-date. This means including all of your education, experience, skills, and achievements. It's important to showcase your strengths and make it easy for potential employers to understand what you have to offer.</p>
				<br>
				<h3 style="font-size:18px;text-align:left;color:black">Customize your resume :</h3>
				<p style="font-size:16px;color:black">Tailor your resume to the job you are applying for. This means highlighting your relevant skills and experience that match the job requirements. Make sure your resume stands out by using bullet points, strong action verbs, and quantifiable results.</p>
				<br>
				<h3 style="font-size:18px;text-align:left;color:black">Use keywords :</h3>
				<p style="font-size:16px;color:black">Use relevant keywords in your resume and job application to increase your chances of being shortlisted by the employer. Many companies use applicant tracking systems (ATS) to filter resumes, so using keywords from the job description can help your resume get past the initial screening.</p>
				<br>
				<h3 style="font-size:18px;text-align:left;color:black">Apply early :</h3>
				<p style="font-size:16px;color:black">Apply for the job opening as soon as possible after it is posted to increase your chances of being considered for the position. Many job openings receive a large number of applications, so it's important to apply early before the employer has already filled the position.</p>
				<br>
				<h3 style="font-size:18px;text-align:left;color:black">Set up job alerts :</h3>
				<p style="font-size:16px;color:black">Set up job alerts on the job portal to receive notifications about new job openings that match your skills and experience. This can save you time by not having to manually search for new job opportunities.</p>
				<br>
				<h3 style="font-size:18px;text-align:left;color:black">Network with other professionals : </h3>
				<p style="font-size:16px;color:black">Connect with other professionals on the job portal to expand your network and learn about new job opportunities. Building relationships with other professionals can lead to new job openings and career advancement opportunities.</p>
				<br>
				<h3 style="font-size:18px;text-align:left;color:black">Apply to multiple jobs :</h3>
				<p style="font-size:16px;color:black">Apply to multiple job openings that match your skills and experience to increase your chances of finding the right job. It's important to cast a wide net and apply to multiple job openings to increase your chances of finding the right fit.</p>
				<br>
				<h3 style="font-size:18px;text-align:left;color:black">Follow up :</h3>
				<p style="font-size:16px;color:black">Follow up with the employer after applying for the job to express your interest and inquire about the status of your application. Following up can demonstrate your enthusiasm and help keep your application top of mind for the employer.</p>
				<br>
				<h3 style="font-size:18px;text-align:left;color:black"> Be professional :</h3>
				<p style="font-size:16px;color:black">Ensure that your online profile and communications with the employer are professional and appropriate. This means using proper grammar, spelling, and punctuation in your emails and messages. It also means avoiding controversial or sensitive topics in your online profiles or communications.</p>
				<br>
				<h3 style="font-size:18px;text-align:left;color:black">Research the company :</h3>
				<p style="font-size:16px;color:black">Research the company before applying for the job to gain a better understanding of their culture, values, and mission. This can help you tailor your application and demonstrate your fit with the company.</p>
				<br>
				<h3 style="font-size:18px;text-align:left;color:black">Be open to feedback : </h3>
				<p style="font-size:16px;color:black">Be open to feedback from employers and recruiters about your job application and interview performance. Use feedback to improve your job search strategy and increase your chances of landing the job.</p>
				<br>
				<h3 style="font-size:18px;text-align:left;color:black">Keep learning :</h3>
				<p style="font-size:16px;color:black"> Continue to learn and improve your skills and knowledge through training, education, and professional development opportunities. This can help you stay up-to-date with the latest industry trends and increase your value to potential employers.</p>
				<br><br><br>
				
				<h3 style="font-size:17px"> "Remember, applying for jobs through job portals can be a competitive process, but with the right strategy and mindset, you can increase your chances of success. By creating a complete and customized profile, networking with other professionals, and preparing for the interview, you can stand out from the crowd and land your dream job. Stay patient, stay positive, and keep learning, and you will be on your way to career success!"</h3>
			
				
			
